BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EvTuUrwitfX_DMIx9sEfK
SUMMARY:Earth Month Event | Mindfulness Walk
DTSTAMP:20260327T031057Z
DTSTART:20260407T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Earth Month with a Mindfulness Walk in the Park!\n\nT
	aking inspiration from the Japanese idea of shinrin-yoku \\(forest bathin 
	g\\)\, we will be hosting a series of mindfulness walks in Pioneer Park. M
	indfulness walking in the forest has shown to have a myriad of benefits fr
	om  improving heart health to reducing stress \\(https://www.npr.org/2023/
	08/22 /1195337204/a-guide-to-forest-bathing\\).\n\nForest Steward Marilyn 
	Cornwe ll \\(https://www.soulscapes.us/\\) will be leading an hour-long gu
	ided walk t hrough the park. Please join us if your curious about mindfuln
	ess\, want to learn more about and experience healing powers of being in n
	ature\, and/or if you want to deepen your connection with Pioneer Park and
	 others.\n\n When:  Tuesday\, April 4th\, 11am-12pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park
	 NW\, Meet at the corner of Island Crest Way and SE 68th St. Follow VOLUNT
	EER EVENT Signs \n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in clothes and sh
	oes you will comfo rtable walking and standing in\, as well as water.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-mindfulness
	-walk/18066426/2026-04-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-mindful
	ness-walk/18066426/2026-04-07T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
